h320TerminalMIB.name: h320TerminalMIB

revisions.description: The draft version of the H320 terminal mib

h320TerminalMIB.contactinfo: Joon Maeng VTEL Corp. Postal: 108 Wild Basin Rd. Austin, TX 78746 USA TEL: (512)437-4567 Email: Joon_Maeng@vtel.com
h320TerminalMIB.description: This MIB module supports the functions of an ITU H.320 terminal

LineRates.name: LineRates
LineRates.description: This object represents the line rate capabilities of the H.320 entity. This includes the various line rates that it supports. It is encoded as bits in an octet string as follows: Capability Bit# 64 Kbits/s 0 2x64 Kbits/s 1 3x64 Kbits/s 2 4x64 Kbis/s 3 5x64 Kbits/s 4 6x64 Kbit/s 5 384 Kbits/s 6 2x384 Kbits/s 7 3x384 Kbits/s 8 5x384 Kbits/s 9 1536 Kbits/s 10 1920 Kbits/s 11 128 Kbits/s 12 92 Kbits/s 13 256 Kbits/s 14 320 Kbits/s 15 512 Kbits/s 16 768 Kbits/s 17 1152 Kbits/s 18 1452 Kbits/s 19 Bits are numbered starting with the most significant bit of the first byte being bit 0, the least significant bit of the first byte being bit 7, the most significant bit of the second byte being bit 8, and so on. A one bit encodes that the capability is supported, a zero bit encodes that the capability is not supported.

VideoFormats.name: VideoFormats
VideoFormats.description: This object represents the video capabilities of the H320 entity. This includes the various video algorithms that it supports. It is encoded as bits in an octet string, with the following definitions: Capability Bit # h261CIFVideo 0 h261QCIFVideo 1 h263SQCIFVideo 2 h263QCIFVideo 3 h263CIFVideo 4 h263CIF4Video 5 h263CIF16Video 6 h262SPMLSIFVideo 7 h262SPML2SIFVideo 8 h262SPML4SIFVideo 9 h262MPMLSIFVideo 10 h262MPML2SIFVideo 11 h262MPML4SIFVideo 12 Bits are numbered starting with the most significant bit of the first byte being bit 0, the least significant bit of the first byte being bit 7, the most significant bit of the second byte being bit 8, and so on. A one bit encodes that the capability is supported, a zero bit encodes that the capability is not supported.

AudioTypes.name: AudioTypes
AudioTypes.description: This object represents the audio capabilities of the H320 entity. This includes the various audio algorithms that it supports. It is encoded as bits in an octet string, with the following definitions: Capability Bit # g711-ALaw64KAudio 0 g711-ALaw56KAudio 1 g711-ULaw64KAudio 2 g711-ULaw56KAudio 3 g722-64KAudio 4 g722-56KAudio 5 g722-48KAudio 6 g728Audio 7 g723.1-5.3KAudio 8 g723.1-6.4KAudio 9 g729Audio 10 Bits are numbered starting with the most significant bit of the first byte being bit 0, the least significant bit of the first byte being bit 7, the most significant bit of the second byte being bit 8, and so on. A one bit encodes that the capability is supported, a zero bit encodes that the capability is not supported.

sysDescr.name: sysDescr
sysDescr.description: A textual description of the terminal. This value should include the full name and version identification of the system's hardware type and software.

sysContact.name: sysContact
sysContact.description: The textual identification of the contact person for this managed node, together with information on how to contact this person.

sysLocation.name: sysLocation
sysLocation.description: The physical location of this system. For instance, closet, terminal room and so on

sysH320TerminalUptime.name: sysH320TerminalUptime
sysH320TerminalUptime.description: The amount of time (in hundredths of a second) since this H320 terminal was last initialized. Note that this is different from sysUpTime in MIB-II [ ] because sysUpTime is the uptime of the network management portion of the system.

sysH320TerminalLocalTime.name: sysH320TerminalLocalTime
sysH320TerminalLocalTime.description: The local date and time of day.

sysH320TerminalDiagnostics.name: sysH320TerminalDiagnostics
sysH320TerminalDiagnostics.description: Indicates the results of the last diagnostic routine performed. noResults(1) No diagnostic has yet been performed, passed(2) the diagnostic has been passed, hardwareFault(3) Hardware fault was detected, softwareFault(4) Software fault was detected.

sysH320TerminalIfType.name: sysH320TerminalIfType
sysH320TerminalIfType.description: The interface type on which this terminal can be called. The interface type identified by this value is the same type of as the ifType from Interface Table in RFC1213. It should only use ifTypes - ds1, e1, basicISDN, primaryISDN.

configH320TerminalSiteName.name: configH320TerminalSiteName
configH320TerminalSiteName.description: Name of the site where the H320 terminal is located. For instance, conference room 1 in Austin, or New York, and so on. sysLocation provides the location information for the maintenance people and this object inform where the conference participants are.

configH320TerminalVideoSystem.name: configH320TerminalVideoSystem
configH320TerminalVideoSystem.description: Video format standard used by the terminal

configH320TerminalIPAddress.name: configH320TerminalIPAddress
configH320TerminalIPAddress.description: The IP address of the h.320 terminal.

configH320ISDNSwitchType.name: configH320ISDNSwitchType
configH320ISDNSwitchType.description: Type of ISDN switch interface to the h.320 terminal. Switch types are specified in ISDN-MIB.

configH320ISDNAddrNumber.name: configH320ISDNAddrNumber
configH320ISDNAddrNumber.description: The number of addresses that each terminal has.

configH320AddrIndex.name: configH320AddrIndex
configH320AddrIndex.description: A unique value for each ISDN address entry. the value ranges between 1 and the value of cionfigISDNAddrNumber.

h320CallSiteNumber.name: h320CallSiteNumber
h320CallSiteNumber.description: The number of site entries that this system contains.

h320XferNextIndex.name: h320XferNextIndex
h320XferNextIndex.description: Identifies the next value of h320SiteIndex to be used in a row creation attempt for the h320CallSiteTable. If new rows cannot be created, this object will have a value of 0.

h320CallSiteTable.name: h320CallSiteTable
h320CallSiteTable.description: A list of video conferencing site entries. The total number of site entries is given by the value of h320CallsiteNumber.

h320CallSiteEntry.name: h320CallSiteEntry
h320CallSiteEntry.description: A video conference site row. Rows are created by an SNMP SET request setting the value of h320SiteRowStatus to 'createandGo. Rows are deleted by an SNMP SET request setting the value of h320SiteRowStatus to 'destroy'.

h320SiteIndex.name: h320SiteIndex
h320SiteIndex.description: A unique value for each video conference Site entry. The value ranges between 1 and the value of h320SiteNumber.

h320SiteName.name: h320SiteName
h320SiteName.description: A textual string assigning a name to a video conference system.

h320SiteIfType.name: h320SiteIfType
h320SiteIfType.description: The interface type on which this site can be called. The interface type identified by this value is the same type of as the ifType from Interface Table in RFC1213. It should onlye use ifTypes - ds1, e1, basicISDN, primaryISDN.

h320SiteLineRate.name: h320SiteLineRate
h320SiteLineRate.description: The line rate that the terminal can be called.

h320CallMode.name: h320CallMode
h320CallMode.description: 1 means the remote terminal supports the autoconfiguration. 2 means the manual configuration is required to call the remote terminal. In this case the, following audio, video and data mode shall be used for the manual configuration.

h320VideoMode.name: h320VideoMode
h320VideoMode.description: A video mode for manual configuration.

h320AudioMode.name: h320AudioMode
h320AudioMode.description: An audio mode for manual configuration.

h320ISDNAddrNumber.name: h320ISDNAddrNumber
h320ISDNAddrNumber.description: The number of ISDN addresses needed to make a call to the remote terminal.

h320SiteRowStatus.name: h320SiteRowStatus
h320SiteRowStatus.description: The row status of the entry. This object is required to create or delete rows administratively. An agent implementing this object is not required to support the values 'createAndWait' and 'notInService'.

h320ISDNAddrTable.name: h320ISDNAddrTable
h320ISDNAddrTable.description: A list of ISDN addresses to call the remote site. This is an extended table of the base table h320CallSiteTable.

h320ISDNAddrEntry.name: h320ISDNAddrEntry
h320ISDNAddrEntry.description: A video conference site row. Rows are created by an SNMP SET request setting the value of h320AddrRowStatus to 'createandGo. Rows are deleted by an SNMP SET request setting the value of h320AddrRowStatus to 'destroy'

h320AddrIndex.name: h320AddrIndex
h320AddrIndex.description: A unique value for each ISDN address entry. The value ranges between 1 and the value of h320AddrNumberin the base table.

h320ISDNAddress.name: h320ISDNAddress
h320ISDNAddress.description: A textual string assigning an address of the conference system.

h320AddrRowStatus.name: h320AddrRowStatus
h320AddrRowStatus.description: The row status of the entry. This object is required to create or delete rows administratively. An agent implementing this object is not required to support the values 'createAndWait' and 'notInService'.

controlH320TerminalAdmin.name: controlH320TerminalAdmin
controlH320TerminalAdmin.description: The desired state of the H320 terminal. Setting the value if this object to these values will have the following actions: run(1) The H320 terminal will enter the run state, reset(2) The H320 terminal will reset, diagnose(3) Will activate the diagnostic routine, stop(4) Will halt the H320 terminal.

controlH320TerminalCallSetUp.name: controlH320TerminalCallSetUp
controlH320TerminalCallSetUp.description: Dial another video conference terminal. Set this value to the index of the site of the video conference site you want to dial in the Site Table in the h320CallSignalingMIB and the system will be dialed.

controlH320TerminalCallHangup.name: controlH320TerminalCallHangup
controlH320TerminalCallHangup.description: Hang up the video conference call in progress now.

controlH320EnableLocalLoopback.name: controlH320EnableLocalLoopback
controlH320EnableLocalLoopback.description: Enable or disable local loop back on a video conference system. Local loopbacks loop back the audio, video and data streams in a call. Once looped back, a new call will show up and the user can observe the audio/video/data rates to assure that these components are working properly.

controlH320EnableRemoteLoopback.name: controlH320EnableRemoteLoopback
controlH320EnableRemoteLoopback.description: Enable or disable remote loop back on a video conference system. Remote loopbacks loop back the audio and video streams from the remote system in a call.. When the remote system calls in, a new call will show and the user can observe the audio/video/data rates to assure that these components are coming in properly from the remote system.

h320TerminalDesrGroup.name: h320TerminalDesrGroup
h320TerminalDesrGroup.description: A collection of objects providing the description of the terminal

h320TerminalConfgGroup.name: h320TerminalConfgGroup
h320TerminalConfgGroup.description: A collection of objects providing the ability to configure the terminal

h320TerminalCallSitesGroup.name: h320TerminalCallSitesGroup
h320TerminalCallSitesGroup.description: A collection of objects providing the information about the site the terminal can call

h320TerminalControlGroup.name: h320TerminalControlGroup
h320TerminalControlGroup.description: A collection of objects providing the ability to invoke terminal functions

h320TErminalCompliance.name: h320TErminalCompliance
h320TErminalCompliance.description: The set of objects required for compliance
